    "reasoning": "The module implements an 8-bit shift register with synchronous enable. When enable is high, on clock edges, S shifts into Q[0], and each Q[i] takes the value of Q[i-1]. When enable is low, the register holds. The multiplexer selects Q based on the 3-input ABC. All inputs are one bit. Using non-blocking assignments for sequential logic. Ports declared as logic. For the shift register, Q is initialized to 0. Multiplexer logic uses combinational always block with @(*). The output Z is determined by ABC via a case statement. Ensure 8 flip-flops with correct indexing. The shift direction: S is the input to Q[0], so shifting in from the left. ABC determines the output via 3-to-8 mux.",
    "module": "module TopModule(clk, enable, S, A, B, C, Z);\n    input clk;\n    input enable;\n    input S;\n    input A;\n    input B;\n    input C;\n    output logic Z;\n\n    // 8-bit shift register\n    logic [7:0] Q;\n\n    // Shift register logic\n    always @(posedge clk) begin\n        if (enable) begin\n            Q <= {Q[6:0], S}; // Shift left, S enters at LSB (Q[0] becomes new S, Q[1] shifts left...)\n        end else begin\n            Q <= Q; // Optional, can be omitted as it's the default\n        end\n    end\n\n    // Combinational logic for mux\n    always @(*) begin\n        case({A, B, C})\n            3'b000: Z = Q[0];\n            3'b001: Z = Q[1];\n            3'b010: Z = Q[2];\n            3'b011: Z = Q[3];\n            3'b100: Z = Q[4];\n            3'b101: Z = Q[5];\n            3'b110: Z = Q[6];\n            3'b111: Z = Q[7];\n            default: Z = 0; // Default case to avoid latch\n        endcase\n    end\n\nendmodule"
